program.name: Family Planning Presumptive Eligibility (FPPE)
program.description:
Family Planning Presumptive Eligibility (FPPE) provides immediate, temporary coverage for family planning services. Services include birth control, advice, and testing. To sign up, visit a Family Planning (FP) provider and answer a few questions.  They will ask about your residency, income, and pregnancy status. No documentation required, only verbal statements. You do not have to be a citizen or legal immigrant to receive coverage. You do not need a social security number.

Apply for the HFS Family Planning Program for ongoing coverage.
program.website_description: Immediate temporary reproductive health and family planning coverage
